---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { url } from '../utils';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Contact"
  description="Contact the Hospital Acupuncture Implementation Framework (HAIF) team at RMIT University."
  lastReviewed="April 2026"
>
  <h1>Contact Us</h1>

  <p>
    Have a question about the Hospital Acupuncture Implementation Framework?
    We welcome enquiries from clinicians, administrators, researchers, and
    acupuncture practitioners interested in hospital-based implementation.
  </p>

  <div class="bottom-line">
    <strong>Get in Touch</strong>
    <p>
      Email: <strong>panda@rmit.edu.au</strong>
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>What We Can Help With</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Questions about applying the HAIF framework at your institution</li>
    <li>Requests for collaboration or research partnerships</li>
    <li>Media and speaking enquiries</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How You Can Help Us</h2>
  <p>
    We invite teams who have implemented acupuncture in hospital settings to
    submit their cases to us &mdash; to showcase successes, share lessons
    learned, and help build the evidence base for hospital acupuncture
    implementation worldwide.
  </p>
  <p>
    Your feedback on framework content, the style of presentation, and
    usability is most welcome.
  </p>

  <h2>Institutional Affiliation</h2>
  <p>
    HAIF is a collaborative innovation between
    <a href="https://www.rmit.edu.au">RMIT University</a> and
    <a href="https://www.nh.org.au">Northern Health</a>, led by
    Professor Zhen Zheng in the School of Health and Biomedical Sciences
    at RMIT.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
